  .row.padding-bottom-medium.padding-top-medium
    .medium-6.columns.feature-highlight.right
      h2#graphite Graphite Support
      p
        | Grafana includes a built in Graphite query parser that takes writing graphite metric expressions
        |  to a whole new level. Expressions are easier to read and faster to edit than ever.
      ul
        li Click on any metric segment to change it
        li Quickly add functions (search, typeahead)
        li Click on a function parameter to change it
        li Move function order to the left or right
        li Direct link to Graphite function documentation
        li Rich templating support
    .medium-6.columns
      a class="gallary-image" href="/assets/img/graphite/editor.png" title="Graphite Editor" data-gallery="1"
        img src="/assets/img/graphite/editor.png" alt="Graphite Editor"

  .row.padding-bottom-medium.padding-top-medium
    .medium-6.columns.feature-highlight
      h2#elasticsearch Elasticsearch Support
      ul
        li Rich query editor with automatic property name lookup
        li Extract many types of metrics from documents like: Avg, Min, Max, Percentiles, Std Dev, etc.
        li Group by multiple terms or filters
        li Query only relevant indicies based on time pattern
        li Alias patterns for short readable series names

    .medium-6.columns
      a class="gallary-image" href="/assets/img/features/elasticsearch_metrics_ex1.png" title="Elasticsearch example" data-gallery="1"
        img src="/assets/img/features/elasticsearch_metrics_ex1.png" alt="Elasticsearch example"

  .row.padding-bottom-medium.padding-top-medium
    .medium-6.columns.feature-highlight.right
      h2 Template Variables
      p
        | Define template variables that can be filled with values dynamically from your
        |  time series store. Use these variables in your metric queries to create
        |  generic and reusable dashboards.
      ul
        li Set variable values via URL
        li Use variables in metric queries
        li Use variables in panel titles
        li Use variables in function parameters

    .medium-6.columns
      a class="gallary-image" href="/assets/img/features/templating_ex1.png" title="Templating" data-gallery="1"
        img src="/assets/img/features/templating_ex1.png" alt="Templating"

